President Obama announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key administration posts. Capricia Penavic Marshall is nominated for Chief of Protocol at the Department of State. She has had an extensive career in public service and has worked with President Clinton and Senator Hillary Clinton. Evan Segal is nominated for Chief Financial Officer at the United States Department of Agriculture. He has experience in the manufacturing industry and is involved in philanthropic work. Rocco Landesman is nominated for Chairman of the National Endowment for the Arts. He has been President of Jujamcyn Theaters and has produced successful Broadway shows. President Obama also announced that Gregory B. Jaczko will be designated as Chairman of the U.S. Nuclear Regulatory Commission. Jaczko has been a Commissioner at the NRC since 2005 and has focused on transparency and public involvement in decision-making.